<HEADLINE>
Nigerian President in Japan <TIMEX2 val="2000-07-18" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">Next Tuesday</TIMEX2>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Abuja <TIMEX2 val="2000-07-15" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">7-15</TIMEX2> (AFP) -

The Nigerian presidency announced <TIMEX2 val="2000-07-15" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">today</TIMEX2> <TIMEX2 val="2000-07-15" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">Saturday</TIMEX2> that President
Olosigun Obasanjo would head for Japan <TIMEX2 val="2000-07-18" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">next Tuesday</TIMEX2> as part of a tour
which will include South Korea and Turkey.


The source added that the delegation of officials and journalists
accompanying the president would leave Abuja <TIMEX2 val="2000-07-15TEV" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">this evening</TIMEX2> <TIMEX2 val="2000-07-15" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">Saturday</TIMEX2>.


No information about the schedule has been released but it is
expected that the Nigerian president will give a speech at the Group
of Eight Summit (the seven main industrialized countries and Russia)
to be held <TIMEX2 val="2000-07-21" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">July 21</TIMEX2>-<TIMEX2 val="2000-07-23" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">23</TIMEX2> in Okinawa (Japan) where he will ask for
international backing for his country's economic program.


Obasanjo will continue his campaign to reduce Nigeria's foreign debt
(in excess of 30 billion dollars).


The Nigerian president is expected to return to his country at <TIMEX2 val="2000-W29" mod="END" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="this might be week 30. If the conference runs until the 23rd, and he's going to visit S. Korea and Turkey after that.">the
end of next week</TIMEX2> after visiting South Korea and Turkey.
</TEXT>
